# Cursor Project Guide — new-api

> Core project rules (JSON wrappers, DB compatibility, protected info, DTO pointer semantics, etc.) are defined in the root-level `CLAUDE.md` and `AGENTS.md`, which Cursor auto-loads. This file only adds Cursor-specific guidance and corrects tech-stack details.

## Tech Stack (current)

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Backend | Go 1.22+, Gin, GORM v2 |
| Frontend framework | React 19, TypeScript |
| Build tool | Rsbuild |
| UI & styling | Radix UI, Lucide React, Tailwind CSS, clsx / cva |
| Data & routing | @tanstack/react-query, @tanstack/react-router, @tanstack/react-table |
| State | Zustand |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Zod |
| i18n | i18next + react-i18next |
| Charts | @visactor/vchart + @visactor/react-vchart |
| Package manager | Bun |
| Databases | SQLite, MySQL, PostgreSQL (all three) |
| Cache | Redis (go-redis) + in-memory |

## Frontend i18n (updated)

- Translation files: `web/default/src/i18n/locales/{en,zh,fr,ja,ru,vi}.json`
- Format: flat JSON under `"translation"` key; **keys are English source strings**
- Base locale: `en`, fallback: `zh`
- Usage: `const { t } = useTranslation()` → `t('English key')`
- Sync script: `bun run i18n:sync` (from `web/default/`)

## Frontend conventions

Detailed frontend development standards (components, state, routing, forms, styling, accessibility, etc.) are in `web/default/AGENTS.md`. Key points:

- Always use `useTranslation()` in React components for i18n
- Prefer `props.xxx` over destructuring for component props
- Run `bun run typecheck` after TypeScript changes
- Use Tailwind utility classes; dynamic classes via `cn()`
- Functional components + hooks only; split files > 200 lines
